00:14:53.639 --> 00:14:54.157
and all that,

00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:55.917
but after some research,

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:58.477
I found something called file descriptors.

00:14:58.560 --> 00:15:00.120
So for those of you who don't know,

00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:03.556
everything in Linux is a file in the file system.

00:15:03.639 --> 00:15:06.637
Everything from hardware devices to network devices

00:15:06.720 --> 00:15:09.280
to documents, they're all files.

00:15:09.759 --> 00:15:10.157
And I thought,

00:15:10.240 --> 00:15:13.957
all right, so I can pipe this byte array into the

00:15:14.040 --> 00:15:16.400
file descriptor of my USB device.

00:15:16.920 --> 00:15:18.116
And I did some searching around,

00:15:18.199 --> 00:15:20.800
and of course, because there is something for

00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:21.876
everything there,

00:15:21.959 --> 00:15:25.837
there's an npm package for this.

00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:29.637
And I was able to plug this npm package,

00:15:29.720 --> 00:15:33.720
say, all right, open up that USB file interface

00:15:33.920 --> 00:15:38.120
and with that, I'm able to simply write to it.

00:15:38.759 --> 00:15:39.839
Isn't that amazing?

